.TH "sprd_mcdt_chan_dma_enable" 9 "sprd_mcdt_chan_dma_enable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sprd_mcdt_chan_dma_enable \- enable the DMA mode for the MCDT channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sprd_mcdt_chan_dma_enable
.BI "(struct sprd_mcdt_chan *chan "  ","
.BI "enum sprd_mcdt_dma_chan dma_chan "  ","
.BI "u32 water_mark "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chan" 12
the MCDT channel
.IP "dma_chan" 12
specify which DMA channel will be used for this MCDT channel
.IP "water_mark" 12
water mark to trigger a DMA request
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Enable the DMA mode for the MCDT channel, that means we can use DMA to
transfer data to the channel fifo and do not need reading/writing data
manually.

Returns 0 on success, or an error code on failure.
